HEADWORD: Overhear
<hw>O`ver*hear"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overheard</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overhearing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>oferhi⟦eacute⟧ran</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To hear more of (anything) than was intended to be
heard; to hear by accident or artifice.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To hear again.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overheat</ent>⟦br⟧
